Phase 2, Week 1 (Onsite Week 4, Overall Week 13) - ActiveRecord, Sinatra, CRUD, RESTful Routes, Heroku, BCrypt

  Process at DevBootcamp
    If you're just re-setting up a db that had already been defined with migrations and seed
      bundle install  # to install all needed gems as listed in Gemfile and Gemfile.lock
      bundle exec rake db:create  # you can use 'be' instead of 'bundle exec'
      be rake db:migrate
      be rake db:seed
      
    be shotgun config.ru  # Start the sinatra server using shotgun re-loader

  ActiveRecord
    ADVANCED ActiveRecord Associations: http://www.theodinproject.com/ruby-on-rails/active-record-associations
    ActiveRecord Query Interface: http://guides.rubyonrails.org/active_record_querying.html
  
  Sinatra
    Sinatra - Classy web-development dressed in a DSL (official / canonical repo): https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra
    
  CRUD & RESTful Routes
